ladeshi male film actors]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the National Film Awards (Bangladesh)]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Symon Sadik\n| image              = Symon Sadik (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Symon in 2018\n| other_names        = Gentle Star\n| birth_date         = 30 August 1985\n(Age 34 years)\n| birth_place        = Kalapara, [[Kishoreganj]], [[Bangladesh]]\n| education          = [[Kishoregonj Government Boys' High School]]\n| occupation         = \u2022 [[Film Actor]]\n\u2022 [[Model (person)|Model]]\n\u2022 [[Politician]]\n\u2022 [[Assistant director]]\n| yearsactive        = 2012\u2013present\n| notable_works      = \u2022 [[Ji Hujur]] \n\u2022 [[PoraMon]]\n\u2022 Er Beshi Valobasha Jay Na\n\u2022 Tomar kache Rini \n\u2022 Chupi Chupi Prem\n\u2022 [[Black Money]] \n\u2022 Mayabini\n\u2022 Tui Amar \n\u2022 [[Jannat (2018 film)]]\n| style              = \u2022 [[Romance film|Romantic]]\n\u2022 [[Comedy]]\n\u2022 [[Action film|Action]]\n\u2022 [[Drama]]\n| height             = 1.73 m\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Deepa Sadik|2014}}\n| partner            = Mohammed Sadikur Rahman, Umme Kulsum\n| children           = 2\n| awards             = \u2022 Bioscope Borsho-Sera Awards in (2013)\n\n\u2022 [[Babisas Award]] for Featured Actor Male in (2016)\n\n\u2022 [[Bangladesh National Film Award for Best Actor]] (2018)\n| nationality        = [[Bangladeshi]]\n}}  \n\n'''Symon Sadik''' is a Bangladeshi film Actor Known for his Works in [[Dhallywood|Dhallywood Cinema]]. And He was an [[assistant director|Assistant Director]] and worked with [[Zakir Hossain Raju]]. He made his debut as a lead in the 2012 Bangladeshi film ''[[Ji Hujur]], Directed by [[Zakir Hossain Raju]], And opposite [[Sara Zerin]]. And his second film [[PoraMon]], Directed by [[Zakir Hossain Raju]] and opposite [[Mahiya Mahi]]. And he won Bioscope Borsho-Sera Awards for Best acting in [[PoraMon]].'' And He also won [[Bangladesh National Film Award for Best Actor]] for his role in the film ''[[Jannat (2018 film)|Jannat]]'' (2018).\n\n==Career==\n[[Symon Sadik]] was born on August 30, 1985, at Kalapara, Kishoreganj, Bangladesh. He rose up in the Kishoreganj Sadar. [[Symon Sadik|Symon]] passed SSC from Kishoreganj Govt. Boys School. He was so much passionate about media arena from early childhood and eventually participated in the Super Hero and Heroin competition organized by NTV.\n\n[[Symon Sadik]] and [[Sara Zerin]]  started in 2012 with director Zakir Hossain Raju in [[Ji Hujur|Ji Huzur]] movie. Later, he was introduced to the audience by starring in the successful movie [[PoraMon]] in (2013). [[Symon Sadik]] got his breakthrough in the film [[PoraMon]]. And he also acted in Bangladeshi film Er beshi Valobasha Jay Na (2013), Tui Shudhu Amar, Tomar Kache Rini, 16 Ana Prem, Shopno Chowa in (2014), Chupi Chupi Prem, Black money, Action Jasmine in (2015),Chokher Dekha, Pure Jay Mon, Matir Pori, Ojante Valobasha in (2016), Mayabini, Khash Zamin, Tui Amar in (2017), And He was acted opposite [[Mahiya Mahi]] in the [[Jannat (2018 film)|Jannat]] film on 2018. He was awarded the [[Bangladesh National Film Award for Best Actor]] in the category for his outstanding performance in the film [[Jannat (2018 film)|Jannat]] and he also acted in \"Matal\" movie in (2018)   \n\nAnd  His upcoming movies is [[Ananda Ashru|Ananda Ashro]] (2020) Directed by [[Mostafizur Rahman Manik]] with same team of successful movie [[Jannat (2018 film)|Jannat (2018)]], There was a movie made under the same name [[Anondo Osru|Anondo osru]] in (1997) starring [[Salman Shah (actor)|Salman Shah]] and [[Shabnur]], But there is no similarity in the story of these two films.   \n\nAnd Nodir Buke Chand with opposite [[Pori Moni|PoriMoni]] and Amar Ma Amar Beheshto in (2020)   \n\n==Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|{{Dagger|alt=films that have not yet been released}}\n|Denotes films that have n